import pandas as pd

def summarize(vars, df):
    summary_stats = df[vars].describe().T
    summary_stats = summary_stats[['count', 'mean', 'std', 'min', '25%', '50%', '75%', 'max']]
    summary_stats.columns = ['', 'Mean', 'Standard Deviation', 'Minimum', '25th Percentile', 'Median', '75th Percentile', 'Maximum']
    return summary_stats
